ohha.domain

Class ResponseMapping

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohha.domain.ResponseMapping

  • public class ResponseMapping
extends Object
    This class maps the correct responses of a condition.
    Author:
    Mikko Tiainen A condition can have multiple separate responses and each response "iteration", so to speak, can have multiple correct answers.

      • isCorrect

        public boolean isCorrect(List<String> resps)

        Parameters:
        resps - list of responses.
        Returns:
        if all responses are correct.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object obj)
        Equality of mappings is based solely on the condition. So if two mappings have the same condition, they are considered to be the same mapping. In essence, one condition should only have mapping.
        Overrides:
        equals in class Object
        Parameters:

        Returns:
